            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention discloses a method and a device for hydrogen production by electrolysis of water and carbon dioxide capture, an electrolysis technology is utilized, an acid solution and an alkali solution are formed under the action of a salt bridge, the alkali solution adsorbs dedusted flue gas (carbon dioxide and sulfur dioxide) and then is introduced into air, sulfite is oxidized into sulfate, the influence of sulfur dioxide on a system is removed, and the system quality is improved. And then neutralizing by utilizing an acid solution generated in an anode environment, so as to release carbon dioxide. According to the invention, the influence of SO2 on the CO2 trapping process is solved by using the oxidation effect of air, and the trapping process of carbon dioxide in flue gas is not influenced by particulate matters and sulfur dioxide; electrolyzed water is used for generating oxygen and green energy hydrogen, and energy supplemented in the solvent regeneration process is reasonably utilized; and green electricity (solar power generation/wind power generation and the like) can be utilized in the electrolysis process, so that indirect emission of carbon dioxide in the regeneration process is avoided."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明公开了一种电解水制氢联合二氧化碳捕集的方法及装置，利用电解技术，在盐桥的作用下形成酸、碱两部分溶液，碱性溶液吸附经除尘后的烟气(二氧化碳、二氧化硫)后通入空气，将亚硫酸根氧化为硫酸根，去除二氧化硫对于系统的影响，后利用阳极环境生成的酸性溶液中和，进而将二氧化碳释放出来。本发明利用了空气的氧化作用解决了SO2对CO2捕集过程的影响，实现了烟气中二氧化碳的捕集过程不受颗粒物和二氧化硫的影响；利用电解水产生氧气和绿色能源氢气，合理利用溶剂再生过程中补入的能量；且电解过程可以利用绿电(太阳能发电/风能发电等)，避免了再生过程中间接二氧化碳的排放。"
                }
            ]
        }
